  "doc_id": "11944",
  "text": "Using GEP to determine the COO of DLBCL is undoubtedly the golden standard, but it requires fresh-frozen material. Thus, it is also of great importance in order to determine the COO with high accuracy on FFPE material, since fresh-frozen material is rarely available in clinical practice. [CITATION_1] Visco-Young algorithm uses a five-marker model of CD10, GCET1, FOXP1, MUM1, and BCL6. [CITATION_2] Nevertheless, no IHC algorithm will be 100% concordant with GEP regarding COO, and no IHC algorithm has so far been able to identify the UC cases. Thus, determining COO by GEP is the only way to identify the UC cases.",
